<doc id="5673" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=5673" title="Comedian Dave Allen dies aged 68">
Comedian Dave Allen dies aged 68

The famous Irish has died aged 68. Known as the "Sit-down comedian," Allen was among the first to base his dry wit humour around the comic practices of large organisations and institutions such as the . 
Born in Dublin in 1936, he later moved to England to pursue his career. He initially was a , but later entered comedy. His fame peaked in the 1970s and 1980s with the "BBC" TV shows "The Dave Allen Show" and "Dave Allen at Large."
He is survived by his wife Karin, and their three children.

